{"TopicId":215069,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Problem whit simpit and Arduino DUE","CreatedByName":"droka","CreatedById":227806,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-15T08:40:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"droka","CreatedById":227806,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-15T08:40:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have copied the controller from \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/103740-wurmi/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022103740\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/103740-wurmi/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Wurmi\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0and would now like to upgrade it to simpit and an Arduino DUE.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately, I always get this message when I try to install it, and the message also appears in the examples.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nc:\\arduino\\libraries\\KerbalSimpit\\src\\KerbalSimpit.cpp: In member function \u0027bool KerbalSimpit::init()\u0027:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nc:\\arduino\\libraries\\KerbalSimpit\\src\\KerbalSimpit.cpp:54:54: error: \u0027SERIAL_RX_BUFFER_SIZE\u0027 was not declared in this scope\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nprintToKSP(\u0022Buffer receive size : \u0022 \u002B String(SERIAL_RX_BUFFER_SIZE));\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n^\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone have a solution?\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-15T09:51:23Z\u0022 title=\u002203/15/2023 09:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 15, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by droka\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-15T14:38:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a compiler error, it means there\u0027s a problem with the C\u002B\u002B source code you\u0027re trying to compile.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked for KerbalSimpit, but I found C# code and different user names.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you share a link to whatever it is you\u0027re doing?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-15T15:00:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224259294\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215069\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678869612\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022227806\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022droka\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, droka said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have copied the controller from \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/103740-wurmi/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022103740\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/103740-wurmi/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Wurmi\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0and would now like to upgrade it to simpit and an Arduino DUE.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately, I always get this message when I try to install it, and the message also appears in the examples.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nc:\\arduino\\libraries\\KerbalSimpit\\src\\KerbalSimpit.cpp: In member function \u0027bool KerbalSimpit::init()\u0027:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nc:\\arduino\\libraries\\KerbalSimpit\\src\\KerbalSimpit.cpp:54:54: error: \u0027SERIAL_RX_BUFFER_SIZE\u0027 was not declared in this scope\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nprintToKSP(\u0022Buffer receive size : \u0022 \u002B String(SERIAL_RX_BUFFER_SIZE));\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n^\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone have a solution?\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need to add Serial support to your project.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck the documentation here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.arduino.cc/reference/en/language/functions/communication/serial/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.arduino.cc/reference/en/language/functions/communication/serial/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFollows a nice tutorial about how to handle serial communications with an Arduino. I think it will worth reading it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.ladyada.net/learn/arduino/lesson4.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.ladyada.net/learn/arduino/lesson4.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"droka","CreatedById":227806,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-15T15:14:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224259436\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215069\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678891087\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a compiler error, it means there\u0027s a problem with the C\u002B\u002B source code you\u0027re trying to compile.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked for KerbalSimpit, but I found C# code and different user names.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you share a link to whatever it is you\u0027re doing?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have rebuilt this controller, now I would like to use simpit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reddit.com/r/KerbalControllers/comments/fm1wk4/updated_my_controller_to_an_arduino_due_displays/?utm_source=share\u0026amp;utm_medium=android_app\u0026amp;utm_name=androidcss\u0026amp;utm_term=1\u0026amp;utm_content=share_button\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EController von Wurmi\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Richi0D/KerbalController-Simpit\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ECode f\u00FCr Controller\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I can\u0027t get the sketch onto the Arduino. Even the examples in the simpit library don\u0027t work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022187168\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Lisias\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Thanks, I will have a look at it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-16T02:40:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224259453\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215069\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678893293\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022227806\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022droka\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, droka said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have rebuilt this controller, now I would like to use simpit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reddit.com/r/KerbalControllers/comments/fm1wk4/updated_my_controller_to_an_arduino_due_displays/?utm_source=share\u0026amp;utm_medium=android_app\u0026amp;utm_name=androidcss\u0026amp;utm_term=1\u0026amp;utm_content=share_button\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EController von Wurmi\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Richi0D/KerbalController-Simpit\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ECode f\u00FCr Controller\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I can\u0027t get the sketch onto the Arduino. Even the examples in the simpit library don\u0027t work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFound it! You need to add a module to the project:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Richi0D/Kerbalcontroller\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Richi0D/Kerbalcontroller\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOut of curiosity, the missing define is on this file:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Richi0D/Kerbalcontroller/blob/master/KerbalController.ino\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Richi0D/Kerbalcontroller/blob/master/KerbalController.ino\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}